  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN123.2-kilavi">C2+3+9v: talaimaka ṉiṭaiccurattut taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu. paṭivameṉṟatu viratam.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE said to his own heart in the middle of the desert. (paṭivam [is] an observance).</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN123.2">
              <l><supplied>uṇṇā maiyi ṉuṟaṅkiya maru</supplied>ṅki</l>
              <l>ṉāṭāp paṭivat tāṉṟōr pōla</l>
              <l>varaicēr ciṟuneṟi niraipuṭaṉ celluṅ</l>
              <l>kāṉa yāṉaik kaviṉaḻi kuṉṟa</l>
              <l>miṟantuporu ṭaruta<supplied>lu māṟṟāy ciṟanta</supplied></l>
              <l><supplied>cillaiṅ kūnta</supplied> ṉallakam porunti</l>
              <l>yoḻiyiṉ vaṟumai yañcuti yaḻitaka</l>
              <l>vuṭaiyai vāḻiye ṉeñcē nilaveṉa</l>
              <l>neykaṉi neṭuvī ḻeḵki<supplied>lai yimaikku</supplied></l>
              <l><supplied>maḻaimaruḷ paḵṟō</supplied>ṉ māvaṇ cōḻar</l>
              <l>kaḻaimāy kāvirik kaṭaṉmaṇṭu peruntuṟai</l>
              <l>yiṟavoṭu vantu kōtai peyarum</l>
              <l>peruṅkaṭa lōtam <supplied>pōla</supplied></l>
              <l><supplied>voṉṟiṟ koḷḷāy ce</supplied>ṉṟutaru poruṭkē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>You who cannot even bring wealth, traversing</l>
                <l>the hills where beauty has perished, with forest elephants</l>
                <l>that go in formation on the little path near the mountains, (3-5)</l>
                <l>resembling noble men in the austerity of not bathing</l>
                <l>with [their] sides that are wearied because of not eating,(1-2)</l>
                <l>if you stayed behind,</l>
                <l>joined to the good bosom of [her with] excellent few tresses [styled in] five [ways]</l>
                <l rend="indent4">you would be afraid of poverty. You would be</l>
                <l>fit to perish, oh my heart, (5d-8c)</l>
                <l>– because of the wealth to be brought by going, you who do not take up one thing,</l> 
                <l>resembling the flood of the great ocean</l>
                <l>that comes with prawn and goes back with garlands</l>
                <l>on the big ghat rushed at by the sea of the Kāviri where vanish bamboo [poles](11-12)</l>
                <l>of the great, generous Cōḻas with many cloud-like shields</l>
                <l>where the long descending sharp [spear] tips on which oil has melted, blink like moonlight. (8d-10)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
